# No Hardcoding Rules

## Overview
Comprehensive guidelines to eliminate hardcoded values and ensure all dynamic data is managed through centralized configuration files.

---

## 1. What Should NEVER Be Hardcoded

### 1.1 Complete Checklist
```
NEVER Hardcode:
├── Strings
│   ├── UI Labels (buttons, headings, labels)
│   ├── Error messages
│   ├── Success messages
│   ├── Placeholder text
│   └── Validation messages
│
├── Numbers
│   ├── Pagination limits
│   ├── Timeout values
│   ├── Retry counts
│   ├── Animation durations
│   └── Breakpoint values
│
├── Styling
│   ├── Colors (hex, rgb)
│   ├── Font sizes (px, rem)
│   ├── Spacing values
│   └── Z-index values
│
├── API/Config
│   ├── API endpoints
│   ├── API keys/secrets
│   ├── Base URLs
│   └── Feature flags
│
└── Business Logic
    ├── Status values
    ├── Role names
    ├── Service types
    └── Pricing logic
```

